text:
1. I don't know if you realized it, but the powerups get more expensive for each 'buy' you did, therefore it is best if you buy the most expensive ones first.
2. Not sure if someone said already said it, but if you manage to kill the reaper you unlock a special character, however that process is not really fun, as it involves staying in one place for 30 minutes without moving and 'playing'. The reapers HP are calculated with your level at the point of spawning it. ~655k * your level, so yes it is beatable, but not really in a normal playthrough. Penta and the necklace loot won't kill the reaper, Penta does 666 damage and I believe the necklace that kills all on screen is kinda the same. On this note, I won't spoil the stats of the character, if anyone is interested just look it up, if I recall correctly the wiki should have a link to guide on how to beat the reaper, but as I said before, that isn't really a fun experience and it isn't promoted in the achievements.
